Rating: 4
I made these today, followed the recipe exactly and they are fabulous!. Nice shiny, crackled exterior and moist interior. In reading the problems some cooks had with the texture of the batter, I offer some suggestions. Let the melted chocolate/egg mixture cool down before you add it to the batter. Make sure you use large eggs, not extra large eggs. Beat the egg, sugar, coffee mixture as directed until it is thick...it took about six minutes with my KitchenAid. When you add the flour mixture, stir only until combined, not longer. Same with chips/walnuts. Bake only one sheet of cookies at a time. I think if you do all of this, you will not have runny batter. My batter was thick and when I scooped out the last of it, it had become almost fudge like in consistency, There really is no need to chill it.The cookies retained their shape and are about 2 inches diameter and 1/2 inch thick.

