Rating: 3
*EXPECT RUNNY BATTER* and you will be ok.When the first batch was in the oven, I noticed that the batter had thickened up some for the next batch.The first batch came out flat and difficult to get off the cookie sheet after 1 minute of cool down time. The second batch was a little puffed and easier to get off the pan. I used my heavy duty shiny aluminum cookie sheets for the first two batches. Well lo and behold the third batch had thickened quite a bit therefore they came out puffed and beautiful! I also had my heavy dark aluminum cookie sheet for third batch. I wonder if the cookie sheet makes any difference? I will make these again now that I know to let the batter thicken.

